reviewText: Both my grandsons (3 & 7 years old) loved this movie, and I would recommend it for all audiences

I asked my 8 year old what he thought of it and how many stars he would give it and he said "a million starts" I had to tell him one to five stars and he said "oh definitely 5 stars" it was cute he said.
My little one said this movie was very good and her favorite part was watching Little Gobie.
It came super fast and my son loves this film!!!!!

While snowboarding, Little Gobie and his beloved pet dragon BeBe get into a hazardous accident and BeBe is badly hurt. When Gobie learns that Santa Claus has the power to help heal his friend, he decides to set off to Santaland in search of Santa Claus to make his special Christmas wish come true.
My 6 and 4 year old boys loved this movie
As a parent Little Gobie is horrible, as a child my 3 year old liked it.
Movie is weird and not very Christmas centered
Exciting and entertaining enough to keep my four year old grandson happy and engaged.
Santa puts that reindeer to the test that seems over the top and cruel.
We have 4 daughters: 10,9,5 &2, they loved the movie!!
Had my kids occupied. Not one of their favorites but it is decent.
